    "text": "The Emancipation Proclamation was signed by President Abraham Lincoln on January 1, 1863 [1]. It declared that all enslaved people in Confederate states 'shall be then, thenceforward, and forever free' [1]. While it did not immediately free all enslaved people, it fundamentally transformed the Civil War into a fight for freedom and paved the way for the 13th Amendment [1].",
    "confidence": 0.95
