    "text": "Here's a grounded introduction that honors the cultural foundation of Kwanzaa:\n\n---\n\n\"Habari Gani! As we gather to celebrate Kwanzaa, we honor not only this season but the continuous thread of wisdom that connects us to our ancestors. Dr. Maulana Karenga created Kwanzaa to introduce and reinforce seven basic values of African culture—values that contribute to building and reinforcing community among African people [1]. These values, the Nguzo Saba or Seven Principles, are not new creations but ancient truths given new voice.\n\nTonight, we light these candles not as mere symbols, but as commitments. Each flame represents a principle our ancestors lived by, struggled for, and passed down so we might thrive. We gather in their honor, in their memory, and in their spirit—knowing that the work of building beloved community continues with each of us.\"\n\n---\n\nThis introduction grounds your speech in the historical purpose of Kwanzaa while maintaining a reverent, ceremonial tone. You can adapt the language to match your specific audience and event.",
