    "text": "The Black Panther Party's Ten-Point Program (1966) outlined their political objectives [1]: (1) Freedom and self-determination, (2) Full employment, (3) End to capitalist exploitation, (4) Decent housing, (5) Education that teaches true history, (6) Free healthcare, (7) End to police brutality, (8) End to wars of aggression, (9) Freedom for all Black prisoners, and (10) Land, bread, housing, education, clothing, justice, and peace [1]. The program concluded with a quote from the Declaration of Independence about the right to alter or abolish oppressive government [1].",
