    "text": "Juneteenth, celebrated on June 19th, commemorates the day in 1865 when Union General Gordon Granger arrived in Galveston, Texas, and announced that all enslaved people were free - two and a half years after the Emancipation Proclamation [1]. This date marks the end of slavery in the United States [1]. Juneteenth became a federal holiday in 2021, recognizing its importance as the nation's second Independence Day and honoring African American freedom and achievement [1].",
